	</ul>
	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/27/Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/27/Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/27/Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-a.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>The interjection 啊 (a) is often added to the end of sentences to add a tone of urgency, exclamation or excitement. However, the exact meaning often  depends on context.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="ASGW66JM#.E5.95.8A_.28a.29_Expressing_Exclamation"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">啊 (a) Expressing Exclamation</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="ASGW66JM#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="ASGW66JM#.E5.95.8A_.28a.29_Expressing_Certainty_or_Urgency"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">啊 (a) Expressing Certainty or Urgency</span></a>
<ul>
